# ⚙️ Cursor Rules — Personal Hub Platform

## 🧱 Architecture Rules

- NEVER mix content logic with UI components
- ALWAYS use typed data (TypeScript)
- DO NOT hardcode content inside components
- All content must come from content layer

---

## 📦 Component Rules

- Components must be:
  - small
  - reusable
  - purpose-driven

- Avoid:
  - large monolithic components
  - deeply nested props
  - unnecessary abstractions

---

## 🎨 UI Rules

- NO unnecessary cards
- NO visual clutter
- NO excessive icons
- NO random colors

- Prefer:
  - whitespace
  - typography hierarchy
  - clean layout

---

## 🧠 Content Rules

- Content structure is defined BEFORE UI
- Each content type must follow its schema
- No flexible/loose data structures

---

## 🚫 Forbidden

- Do NOT create a design system prematurely
- Do NOT introduce global state unless necessary
- Do NOT add animations unless explicitly requested
- Do NOT install extra libraries without reason

---

## ⚡ Implementation Style

- Use simple, clear solutions
- Prefer readability over cleverness
- Avoid premature optimization

---

## 🔍 When unsure

Default to:

- simpler solution
- less code
- clearer structure
